.TH "hmcdrv_ftp_cmd" 9 "hmcdrv_ftp_cmd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hmcdrv_ftp_cmd \- Perform a HMC drive FTP, with data from user-space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" hmcdrv_ftp_cmd
.BI "(char __kernel *cmd "  ","
.BI "loff_t offset "  ","
.BI "char __user *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmd" 12
FTP command string "<cmd> <filename>"
.IP "offset" 12
file position to read/write
.IP "buf" 12
user-space buffer for read/written directory/file
.IP "len" 12
size of \fIbuf\fP (read/dir) or number of bytes to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function must not be called before \fBhmcdrv_ftp_startup\fP was called.
.SH "RETURN"
number of bytes read/written or a negative error code
